E.	 The Emergency Response Program

Brandt has a Consolidated Emergency Response/Contingency Plan that has been included under the California Environmental Reporting System (CERS). The plan lists emergency containment and cleanup procedures, emergency equipment on-site and a list of the telephone numbers of to contact in the event of an emergency. Internal response will occur and evacuation maps are posted on-site. Neighboring facilities that may be affected by an off-site release will be contacted via telephone. The most recent review or update of the emergency response plan will be conducted on January 18th, 2022. Employee training on the Plan took place on January 18th, 2022. The primary local emergency response agency with which the Plan is coordinated is Tulare County Environmental Services (EHS) as well as the Tulare County Fire Department. There is no known other federal or state emergency plan requirements to which the stationary source is subject.

